<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Stamina has no effect on pets... this is a known fact..<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
   No, it is not fact, it is theory only,  but no one has been able to prove or disprove it yet.<br>
<br>
   Personally, I believe it does have an effect, based on my own parses and observations.  As an example, I will use one of my own buffs called Spiritual Brawn.  SB gives +125 MAXHP and 18ATK.  When I cast this on myself, I notice a small drop in health of about 1/5th a bubble, when I cast it on my guild's level 63 main tank, I see a very very minimal blip on his health roughly 1 pixel.  When I cast it on my level 39, 49, 54 warders, I see no change at all, however, when I cast it on my level 9 warder, I see a very slight change in health, approximately 1/8th a bubble.<br>
<br>
   Now, when I use my STA buff on myself, I usually see a drop of about 1/8th bubble, on my guild MT I see no change, unless I had just cast SB above, and no change on my warder, again unless I am using the level 9 warder.<br>
<br>
   From observation and parsing, I have also seen that my warder gains approximately 50 - 75 HP at 54 with the STA buff and 100 - 140 with the SB on.   Of course those numbers can be caused by slight differences in the time it takes to kill my warder versus his regen, but there is really no way to prove or disprove it.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I also think dex/str/agil also has zero effect on pets (But that's just my own opinion)<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
